Program: Outlook
Title: 11/09/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00xnxp9
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 12 Sep 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the former Catholic priest who tried to negotiate peace with the notorious leader of the Lord's Resistance Army, Joseph Kony. Also the Belgian photographer who documented the lives of a Japanese Yakuza crime syndicate. He was told if he disrespected them during his work he would have to cut off his own finger. And the Canadian who spent ten years in the church founded by the Reverend Sun Myung Moon, and took part in a mass wedding ceremony with thousands of others. Show less